text:
TL;DR 
Weightloss has its Positives and Negatives and I guess weird sides. I feel like im in a new body and getting used to it, will is just an experience...thats the only i can really use to describe it. All i can say is i feel better about me.

author: JupiterDropkick92_
text:
On a Strange or Positive Note,
As I lose more weight, the more and more my body wants to be feminine. I have gotten a little more flexible and i can move in ways I always wanted too. There are times I can be a bit too girly tho and I gotta tell myself to calm down.

author: JupiterDropkick92_
text: Aaaand just what the Fuck am I goin on about? I just know that I get more of that vibe from other men, especially dudes with girlfriends or wives. All I know is that this fucks with my anxiety severely. Is this a matter of not caring what others think? Yes. My thing is Why Tho?

author: JupiterDropkick92_
text: Now ive been a jealous person, we all have. Ive been a jealous bf and friend. I'm cool now but its just that I can recognize it and understand cause that was me too.

author: JupiterDropkick92_
text:
On a Negative One,
Yes, I'm not skinny and not gonna pretend I am cause like I said before, I still got some progress to make. It feels like some people think im just doing this to show off or this is something im just doing for the attention..

author: JupiterDropkick92_
text:
On a Positive Note, 
people have given me compliments and encourage me to keep going. I can finally fit back into old shirts or shirts I couldn't wear. I can move and look how I always wanted to look. Theres still more progress to be made but I can honestly say I am doing better

author: JupiterDropkick92_
text: Losing weight has been an somewhat odd experience. In the beginning i just wanted to lose a couple of pounds, I started fitting into smaller shirts and generally started feeling better. Thought "why not?" and start losing weight so I can start looking how i want to..
